.\" termin.al-name: cv
.\" termin.al-usage: cv [--split horizontal|vertical] | cv lock
.\" termin.al-summary: Unlock or open protected CV content.
.TH CV 1 "" "termin.al" "termin.al Manual"
.ftr B R
.ftr I R
.ftr BI R
.SH NAME
cv \- Unlock or open protected CV content.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
cv [--split horizontal|vertical]
cv lock
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
Opens protected CV Markdown inline or in a split. When shared access is locked, requests the viewer key through the non-echoing secret prompt. Owners bypass the shared key.
.PP
.B cv lock
removes shared-CV capability and discards open CV presentation state.
.SH FAILURES
Positional keys and unsupported options are rejected. Invalid, throttled, unavailable or missing CV access reports
.BR "CV access failed." .
.SH NOTES
The viewer key is never accepted as a positional argument, retained in command history, echoed to assistive technology, persisted or logged. CV content is memory-only and uncounted by statistics. The offline demo serves synthetic CV content only.
.SH EXAMPLES
.nf
$ cv
$ cv --split vertical
$ cv lock
.fi
.SH SEE ALSO
login(1), logout(1), open(1)
